# Code Generation Workflow

**Most entity and API code is generated from XML.** Do not hand-edit generated files.

## Workflow

1. **Edit XML** — `../generation/xml/stencil-entities.xml` (from `server/api` workspace)
2. **Run generator** — `cd ../generation/tools && ./code-generator-cli.exe` (config in `code-generator.config.xml`)
3. **Customize extension files only** — `.manager.ts`, `.controller.ts`, `.module.ts`

## Never Edit (STARTFILE — regenerated)

- `*.model.ts`
- `*.schema.ts`
- `*.manager.base.ts`
- `*.controller.base.ts`
- `*.sanitized.validators.ts` (when part of entity generation)
- `list-input-*.ts`
- `entity.module.ts`, `entity.registry.ts`, `account-deletion-manager.ts`
- Generated frontend/API model stubs (`frontend/src/stencil/**/models/**`, `frontend/src/stencil/**/endpoints/**`)
- App layer entity models in `app/src/cloud/models/entities/` (when generated)

## Safe to Edit (ENSUREFILE or hand-written)

- `*.manager.ts` — extension with custom methods
- `*.controller.ts` — extension with custom endpoints
- Entity-specific `*.module.ts` only when confirmed as ENSUREFILE/custom; generated aggregators are STARTFILE
- Feature request models in `backend/src/features/**/models/` — **check if generated**; feature entities may be generated from XML

## Reserved System Fields

`created_utc` and `updated_utc` are reserved system fields — the generator adds them automatically to every document entity. Never define these as business fields in XML. If domain-specific timestamps are needed, use distinct names (e.g. `generated_utc`, `edited_utc`, `invited_utc`).

## Adding a New Entity

1. Add `<item>` with `<field>` elements to XML
2. Run generator
3. Confirm generated `entity.module.ts` and `entity.registry.ts` include it
4. Add custom logic in `{entity}.manager.ts`

## Adding a Field to Existing Entity

1. Add `<field>` to the `<item>` in XML
2. Run generator
3. Update extension files (`.manager.ts`) if needed

## Adding a New Enum

1. Add `<enum>` to XML
2. Run generator

